<p>Walker's Point and the Third Ward showcase Milwaukee's urban renewal with newer construction that often accommodates solar installations easily. These neighborhoods' proximity to downtown makes energy efficiency particularly valuable. Wauwatosa and West Allis suburbs feature larger lots with optimal south-facing roof exposure for solar panels. The North Side's affordable housing stock benefits significantly from solar and HVAC incentive programs, making energy improvements accessible to diverse income levels. Each neighborhood's unique architecture and tree coverage requires customized approaches to maximize solar production and HVAC efficiency.</p>

